. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1275,1423,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head predominantly black, clypeus dark brown; antennae dark brown, testaceous on antennomeres I-III; labium and maxillae light brown, palpomeres light brown to testaceous; mandibles light brown at apex and pale yellow at base; pronotum dark brown at centre, clearing towards borders, margins and angles pale yellow; elytra dark brown with a yellowish to light-brown apical patch; wings dark brown; thorax and abdomen light brown; legs pale yellow to light brown, darker at apex of femora, tibiae and tarsi (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1107,538,563]" captionStart="Figures 1-6" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1356,206,2041]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[151,1360,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1-6:Dorsal habitus ofMacromalthinus species.(1) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(2)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(3)M.orapuensis sp.nov.(4) M.piceiventrissp.nov. (5) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(6)M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384149/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[869,1494,602,1235]" lastBlockId="7.[94,719,218,787]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[869,946,602,627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Males:</emphasis>
Head large, transverse, 1.2 times wider than pronotum; temples elongate, strongly tapering posteriorly; vertex and frons concave. Eyes bulging, oblong, prominent. Antennae filiform,flattened dorso-ventrally, densely covered with thin setae; antennomere I wide, II very short,III 0.6 times shorter than I, IV and V nearly as long as I, VI slightly longer than the following ones, progressively decreasing in length apically. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1322,1383,826,851]" captionStart="Figures 7-12" captionStartId="4.[869,937,1217,1242]" captionTargetBox="[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-697@4.[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 7-12: Pronotum of Macromalthinus species. (7) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (8) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (9) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (10) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (11) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (12) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384151/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) nearly as long as wide; anterior margin slightly arched,lateral margins slightly constricted near anterior angles, sinuate and convergent from anterior half; pronotal surface elevated antero-medially and near posterior angles, forming two lateral shallow grooves, parallel lateral margins, convergent posteriorly. Elytra short, rugulose, densely covered with short and thin setae;sutures dehiscent from posteri- or half; apex slightly swollen dorsally. Fore femur (
<figureCitation box="[1413,1487,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figures 13-18" captionStartId="5.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[97,1416,991,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-354@5.[94,1417,986,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 13-18: Fore femur of Macromalthinus species. (13) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (14) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov.(15) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(16) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(17) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(18) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384153/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) swollen, wider medially, with inconspicuous rounded ventral tooth; femora, tibiae and tarsomeres increasing in length from fore to hind legs; tarsal claws simple, not toothed. Abdominal tergites and sternites sclerotized; ventrites densely covered with long thin setae; glandular pores not prominent; distal margin of ventrite VI entire, not notched, slightly membranous; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[635,712,282,307]" captionStart="Figures 19-24" captionStartId="6.[170,238,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[172,1491,1272,2042]" captionTargetId="figure-506@6.[170,1493,1269,2044]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 19-24:Ventrite VII of males of Macromalthinus species.(19) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(20) M.luteoapicalis sp.nov.(21)M. orapuensis sp.nov.(22) M.piceiventris sp.nov.(23) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(24) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384156/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) H-shaped,lateral margins sinuous,with a broad membranous area anteriorly and a wide posterior notch; ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[146,225,378,403]" captionStart="Figures 25-30" captionStartId="7.[794,862,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[798,1414,205,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-491@7.[794,1418,204,1980]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 25-30: Ventrite VIII of males of Macromalthinus species. (25) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (26) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (27) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(28)M.piceiventrissp.nov.(29) M.quadratithoraxsp.nov.(30) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384158/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, irregularly oblong, strongly convex; a short,oblique ridge near left margin.Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[101,176,442,467]" captionStart="Figures 31-36" captionStartId="8.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1491,674,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[170,1493,670,2012]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 31-36: Aedeagus of Macromalthinus species. (31) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (32) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (33) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (34) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(35) M. quadratithorax sp.nov.(36) M. xerophilus sp.nov. Abbreviations:pt = prolongation of tegmen, sp = setiferous prolongation,rp = right paramere, lp = left paramere,ml = median lobe.Scale bars:0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384160/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) with right prolongation of tegmen broadly projected dorsally, without apophysis on dorsal surface; left setiferous prolongation elongate, wide, with short apical setae; right paramere elongate, straight, apex acute, slightly curved; left paramere elongate, narrow, flat, apex rounded; median lobe straight, broad, apex membranous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[163,495,634,659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus box="[381,492,634,659]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
